metadata.name: RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton #92
metadata.description:
Stephen Wolfram's Elementary Cellular Automaton where 3 different rules are drawn in the Red, Green and Blue color components of the image.

Rules are selected randomly among a pre-selection of 53 rules from which nice behaviors emerge.

Tokens can have a cell size in the [1; 20] range.

metadata.name: Hall of Mirrors #73
metadata.description:
The Hall of Mirrors, a 3D installation using vertex shader and digital feedback.
Inspired by Kraftwerk's song and old house of mirrors funfair attractions from my childhood.

Instructions:
- use the mouse to navigate (zoom, pan and drag)
- press 'c' to switch between multiple camera angles
- press 'b' to play/pause the animation
- press 'p' to download the current view it in a custom resolution (only in live view).

Berlin, December 2021
@bgola

metadata.name: Tangled #196
metadata.description:
"Tangled" is a generative art project that explores the emergent behaviour of simple shapes moving according to a random flow field. While the final result is always constrained to the shape of a circle, the variation within is endless.

Instructions:
Press "p" to pause the animation.
In live mode, press 1 through 5 to save a PNG version of the final result. The following resolutions are available:
1: 400 x 400 (ideal for Twitter PFP)
2: 1000 x 1000
3: 2000 x 2000
4: 4000 x 4000
5: 5000 x 5000
Please be patient, generating the PNG may take some time!

Made with p5.js.

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #322
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.

metadata.name: Syzers #502
metadata.description:
Syzers is a generative synthesizer project with sounds altered by Tone JS.

···· On Tuesday, May 17, unsold editions will be burned ····

Visually it consists of 16 layers, in which more than 350 elements are combined randomly, generating synthesizers with unique environments and landscapes.
As for the sound, 40 tracks were recorded with analog synthesizers that were then assigned to each of the modules. These, combined in groups of 4, provide thousands of possible combinations. 
In addition, these sounds will be further modified by code effects that will randomly vary their properties.

Click to listen to the sounds

Many thanks to @Jpupper and @Fipiaggio for help with programming the sound part and @Purespider for the template. 
"FXHASH PFP Token Generator" https://github.com/PureSpider/fxhash-pfp

for best resolution "open live" then use the "download image" button on the lower right corner ;)

metadata.name: Phantoms #163
metadata.description:
Phantoms is a series of hazy memories of distant places. Some tranquil, others sinister, each scene is as much defined by what is revealed as by what remains unseen.

In this collection I aim to juxtapose hard and soft. Blocky shapes form the core of the compositions. Upon these surfaces, soft textures appear to flow and drip over the sides. Varying levels of opacity, lighting, and fog effects further soften the scenes to create an atmospheric, dream-like quality. By remaining semi-abstract, each of the color palettes are given the space to influence the mood dramatically.

metadata.name: Fractures #101
metadata.description:
Fractures is a personal interpretation of how beauty can emerge from broken shapes.

Starting from a simple and regular geometric shape, Fractures succeeds in breaking the initial visual monotony thanks to a recursive division system applied to the triangles of the initial polygon. Line patterns, random color inversions, grainy and charcoal effect are then added to give the final image a nice organic feel.

Press [P] to generate and save a 4000x4000 .png file. This can take some time, be patient.

Artist: Estienne
Dec 2021

metadata.name: Fractal Flower #225
metadata.description:
In this series I continue my exploration of the Mandelbrot set. This iconic fractal can be tweaked and used to make many different organic looking effects. 

Rarity comes from the following modifiers:
- Star = 10%
- Web = 10%
- Guiding Star = 5%
- Shapeshifter = 5%
- Rippler = 2.5%

metadata.name: I Know #98
metadata.description:
Combining both 3D and 2D techniques to render abstract objects from an iterative folding procedure.
Formula is highly parametrized to provide a great variety of results.

metadata.name: Attractors Bestiary #48
metadata.description:
2D strange attractors have always been fascinating. Created from simple formulas, they are capable of generating a multitude of stunning shapes.

This generative program randomly creates and compiles a multitude of variations of a given attractor type. As a bestiary would show a selection of monsters, this one exposes these mathematical beasts. Each attractor can be viewed in full screen by clicking on it.

The available attractor types are:
- Clifford
- Clifford Squared
- Estienne 1
- Estienne 2
- Bed Head
- Fractal Dream
- Symmetric Icon

Artist: Estienne
Dec. 2021
